  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women-inclusive Enterprises</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-	Increase in accessibility of finance for gender-inclusive businesses:
IFC anticipates that the Project will support TSKB to increase access to finance for women inclusive businesses, with the whole IFC&apos;s proceeds earmarked for this purpose. 
-	Improved outcomes for women employees of borrowing gender-inclusive businesses:
IFC anticipates that the Project will support TSKB&apos;s women inclusive mid-caps to support women employment and to improve the gender score.
-	Inclusiveness: 
By promoting greater gender equality through wider use of gender certification tools by the Bank&apos;s customers, this project will contribute to an increased inclusiveness of the Turkish labor market.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed senior loan of up to US$100 million to Turkiye Sinai Kalkinma Bankasi A.S. (TSKB, or the Bank) aims to support Banks lending to Women-inclusive Enterprises, which are private sector mid-cap companies in Turkey that meet an established gender equality criteria.</narrative>
  </description>
